	"note": "The framework manifest v0: the file set a scaffolded game copies (copy + provenance + offered updates, the library pattern). The rev is COMPUTED, never stored: sha256 over the sorted 'path sha256' lines of every file below, truncated to 12 hex — derivable from the filesystem on both sides (scripts/framework_dist.sh prints it). Scope is FW1's world spine (Chronicle + Almanac + Loom + Elements + the whole Watershed) PLUS the parse-time closure that set honestly drags in (GDScript resolves autoload names at compile time, so the spine's scripts pull the Toolkit, the link, the Campfire spine, items/skills/UI and the player). Marked exclusions are content: valley.tscn, the title, the hound and wildlife, the kit placeholder scenes, quest_lint (test harness, rides FW3), and all of data/ except the default biome palette the importer paints against. The autoload column and the framework sections of project.godot (display, autoload, navigation, shader_globals, input, physics) are copied from THIS repo's project.godot at scaffold time — the column IS the table of contents.",
